SEC. 4. The Institute shall have the following specific powers and functions:

establish and develop bee breeding facilities capable of producing good quality queen bees needed in its training, research and extension programs;

develop, verify and package appropriate apiculture technologies national application;

establish proper quality control systems for honeybee products and by- products and standards for beekeeping tools and equipment;

develop, design and fabricate beekeeping tools and equipment using local materials;

establish wax mills for processing wax foundations sheets out of locally- produced wax from native and exotic honeybee species;

develop effective, efficient technologies for pollen wax, propolis and royal jelly production;

establish and develop model beekeeping communities;

establish and maintain regional satellite centers to serve as extension, research and training arms of the Institute;

establish appropriate and efficacious pest management programs;

develop appropriate, and effective beekeeping extension strategies and approaches;

educate farmers to increase/improve crop yield and quality through bee pollination;

educate farmers to increase/improve crop yield and quality through bee pollination;

utilize beekeeping technologies to revolutionize reforestation, agroforestation, forest protection, rehabilitation and beautification programs; and

establish and define the organizational structure, duties of officials and personnel of the Institute.
